Vice President Kamala Harris and President Alejandro Giammattei of Guatemala discussed joint efforts to manage migration in a humane and orderly manner. They talked about creating new opportunities for legal pathways and implementing robust border security measures. Harris highlighted the progress made in addressing the root causes of migration through the U.S. Strategy to Address the Root Causes of Migration from Central America. Additionally, $44.5 million in U.S. Government funding was announced to combat gender-based violence in the region. Harris also updated Giammattei on efforts to create economic opportunities in Guatemala through a partnership with the private sector, resulting in over $4.2 billion in investments and job creation. Lastly, Harris expressed support for free, fair, inclusive, and peaceful elections in Guatemala.